Blood Disorders Affecting Red Blood Cells. Blood disorders that affect red blood cells include: Anemia: People with anemia have a low number of red blood cells. Mild anemia often causes no symptoms.More severe anemia can cause fatigue, pale skin, and shortness of breath with exertion.lood disorders can affect any of the three main components of blood: 1  Red blood cells, which carry oxygen to the body's tissues. 2  White blood cells, which fight infections. 3  Platelets, which help blood to clot.
